Place.NFS: Nike Field Soccer at Sara D. Roosevelt Park
Place.XIA: Xi'an Famous Foods 西安名吃 | Midtown 45th St.
Place.MAA: NY Martial Arts Academy Midtown Manhattan
Place.CES: Consulate General of El Salvador in New York
Place.TRB: Theodore Roosevelt Birthplace National Historic Site

Activity.BBC: Consume a lollipop as fast as possible. If it cracks you must restart. The lollipop is considered consumed once you can touch the tip of the stick. You may not bite or fracture the lollipop in any way.
Activity.NCC: Confess in detail, in writing, to something you did wrong. Read your confession on camera. The confession must be truthful and, ideally, illegal.
Activity.BSC: Set a timer. Without looking at any timekeeping device, estimate 100 seconds.
Activity.NFS:
Make a paper football. Kick a field goal through your partner's hands from the farthest distance possible.

How to make and kick (ignore section 2) https://newtonma.myrec.com/documents/paper_football_game.pdf
Activity.QUA: Do as many squats as you can. A squat only counts if your thighs achieve at least horizontal.
Activity.XIA:
Select one Biang variant at random. Copy it. Your partner must identify which variant you copied.

https://www.reddit.com/r/ChineseLanguage/comments/uhgai7/all_24_variants_of_the_character_bi%C3%A1ng/#lightbox"
Activity.HPB: Hop in circles on one foot until you lose balance (e.g., foot touching the ground)
Activity.PTH: Recreate any scene from a movie. You must use at least one prop. Double your time if you do not use a script
Activity.NMM: Randomly generate 5 numbers between 1-9, and 2 number between 10-99. Using each number up to once, use math operators (+-/x^) to make the price of any ticket to the museum (in cents)
Activity.HST: Download any compass app. Close your eyes and spin at least 10 times. Place your phone on the ground before opening your eyes, pointing it directly south.
Activity.MFB: Buy a pastry. Separate it into layers. Each layer must be more than half the area of the original pastry
Activity.CHS:
Pronounce one or more Swedish tongue twisters perfectly into Google Translate

https://www.omniglot.com/language/tonguetwisters/swedish.htm
Activity.NYU: Find a book with questions and answers in it. Answer as many as possible correctly. You may not use the same book as any previous team.
Activity.NSF: Identify Fish. The guessing players may not enter the fish section or view any fish labels. Another player must bring them actual fish or photos of fish found in the store. The guessing players must guess the exact name of the fish species. If the players guess the exact name of the fish, the team scores points equal to the price per pound of the fish. If the guessing players guess a broader category of the fish (e.g. bass vs. sea bass), they gets one additional guess to be more specific. Teams may attempt as many fish as they wish, summing the total of correct answers. A fish is defined as any legless animal that lives in the water.
Activity.NYM: Using only your mouth, tie a knot in a cherry stem, noodle, or other flexible food. May be done anywhere in Chinatown
Activity.SPC: At the end of the game, this landmark is assigned to the player who visited the oldest building after visiting this one (not including this building, which is the oldest in NYC). You must be able to prove the age of the building you visited.
Activity.TOL: Call someone and tell them you love them. The person you call cannot be playing this game
Activity.MAA: Break something into two pieces by striking with your hand or foot
Activity.GIH:
The quiz may only be attempted once. Do the quiz together.

https://play.howstuffworks.com/quiz/irish-slang-quiz
Activity.ATL: Play some heavy metal. Head bang for one minute.
Activity.LFU: In a single photo capture as many bronze statues as you can. A statue is any physically distinct piece of bronze in the station.
Activity.GBK: Set a timer for 2 minutes. Achieve an average heartrate of 75 BPM (150 total beats)
Activity.ESB: Take a picture of the Empire State Building from as far away as possible. You must take the picture AFTER visiting the Empire State Building
Activity.LNS: Balence an item simultaneously on two players heads. You may not use anything, including your hands, to affix the object to your head. Touch as many doors as possible without dropping the object. The object is dropped if it loses contact with one persons head.
Activity.MSB:
Take any practice MCAT test
 https://www.test-guide.com/free-mcat-practice-tests.html

You may not take the same test twice
Activity.CES: Choose invest one point in a crypto currency. If at the end of the game it has increased in value, you gain one point. Otherwise, you lose one point. You may not invest more than one point in any currency. You may not invest more points than you currently have. You must declare your investment and the current price while at this location. At the end of the game, this landmark is assigned to the team that earned the most points here. In the case of a tie, the stop is assigned to the player that arrived here first.
Activity.ACF: Pronounce a single German word accurately enough to register in Google Translate
Activity.MGS: Acquire any amount of salt. Sprinkle salt at this and every subsequent challenge location. You must have the salt with you at the end of the game. You do not have to complete a challenge at a landmark to salt it.
Activity.PNS: Ride an escalator for as long as possible. You are permitted to walk in the wrong direction on the escalator to extend your time on it. You may ride any escalator in any building in the general area.
Activity.VSS: Consume as much liquid as possible. You must be able to prove the volume of the liquid.
Activity.WHS: Submerge one hand in ice water in front of the William Seward statue. Water must reach approximately 0C before your hand enters. If all ice melts, it is no longer ice water. Hand must be submerged up to the wrist.
Activity.NTD: Catch Pokemon in Pokemon Go for 5 minutes. You cannot catch the same Pokemon twice.
Activity.TBH: Spend at least 3 minutes in Tibet House. Do not talk or use your phone. Continue not talking or using your phone after you leave, including for game-related activities. Stop your time if you talk or use your phone.
Activity.MLB: Pitch a ball-like object to your partner, who must hit it with a bat-like object as far as possible. Ball and bat may be interpretted loosely.
Activity.BDW: Perform your interpretation of any broadway scene. It must include singing, dancing, props, and costumes. Double your time if you do not use a script.
Activity.GCC:
Converse only in questions without repeats, hesitations, or non-sequitors. Hesitations are any silence longer than 3 seconds
.
Activity.MJM: Perform any Michael Jackson dance. You must match the dancing in the video. Only time spent actually dancing counts.You must get at least 50% of the moves kind of right
Activity.SAD:
Identify Dvorak/not Dvorak from a playlist

https://open.spotify.com/playlist/1bhVTQF3l4zPkjOSdelASM

Play on shuffle
Activity.ESX: One partner picks an item and covers its country of origin. Other teammates must guess where it is from. You may not select an item from the same country twice.
Activity.ESG: Stand on one foot while balancing an object on your other foot, your head, and the back of each hand. If you make it past 1 minute, you must start hopping up and down. The objects must be rigid and unadhered (i.e., no clothes)
Activity.BOB: Guess the number of boba in a drink. You have 15 seconds to make your guess after receiving or viewing your drink. You may not manipulate the boba count in any way when you order.
Activity.QEG:
Translate phrases into American English. Select words randomly without replacement. 

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_British_terms_not_widely_used_in_the_United_States
Activity.WTS: First partner walks from the Statue of Sherman to the Pulitzer Fountain, counting steps while the second partner does NOT watch. Second partner attempts to walk the same route in the same number of steps
Activity.SEX:
Answer Never Have I Ever questions. Share answers in the group chat. 

https://www.buzzfeed.com/elena_hernandez/dirty-never-have-i-ever-questions
Activity.WSP: Find high people. You must either spot the marijuana itself, or receive confirmation from the user that they are high.
Activity.SEP: Pick 3 perfumes. Tell the guesser the names but do not show them the labels. Spray the perfume on the sample sticks and give them to the guesser. If they guess all three correctly, increase your streak by 1, otherwise reset it to 0.
Activity.MAL: One partner picks an item costing over $200. The guesser must guess its price.
Activity.WGG: Write a poem and whisper it to your partner. Use as many rhymes as possible.
Activity.SCA: Learn words from any Scandinavian language. The words must be found somewhere in the museum. Every word you say must register correctly in Google translate. You must say all your words in one go, but can make multiple attempts.
Activity.CAA:
Take any of these quizzes https://alllooksame.com/

You may take multiple quizzes and choose the highest score. You may not take a quiz more than once.
Activity.TRB: Piggy back your partner from one end of the block
Activity.BAR: Survive in any game without adding additional money. You may not add more than the minimum amount of money necessary to start a game.
Activity.MSL: Declare a book title. Find the book. You may use https://borrow.nypl.org/ to confirm that the book is present but not its exact shelf
Activity.NYS: Choose another team. If that team controls more stops than you at the end of the game, you gain two bonus points. Do not claim this stop.
Activity.MMS: Strike a pose while a subway runs under you. Take a picture. Post it on social media. Any form of like-farming is permitted. Likes includes any endorsement that can be submitted once per person (e.g. upvotes, hearts). You may use multiple social media platforms. Control is assessed at the end of the game.
Activity.TRE: Climb a tree as high as possible. Altitude is measured as the distance between the ground and the lowest point of the player.
Activity.TES: Buy a snack and feed it to the guesser. The guesser must guess ingredients present in the snack. He or she may make up to 20 guesses.
Activity.YUM: Hand-write something in Hebrew. It must be correctly translated by Google Translate Lens. Also spend 5 minutes in the museum learning.
Activity.HVP: Construct a free-standing orthodox cross. Your cross can only be supported at the base. It must have all three crossbars, with the top two perpendicular to the ground and the third slightly askew. It must stand unaided for at least 30 seconds.
Activity.GRS: Order noodles. Tie some noodles together. Slurp them all in one go. Knots and noodles must remain intact during the entire slurp. No noodle may be tied to more than two other noodles. You may work as a team only if you do the Lady & Tramp kiss thing at the end.
Activity.HIL: Drop something from Highline, trade place, and repeat.
Activity.CHE: Guess the number of customers who will patronize (spend money at) a shop for 5 min. At least one customer must visit. Your own visit does not count.
Activity.HME:
Play hangman. Your score is the number of missed letters.

Generate your words from: https://randomwordgenerator.com/
Activity.GJA: Each round, pick a random song from one of the two following playlists. The guesser must guess if it is from the Uruguay playlist or the Paraguay playlist. Your score is your longest streak of correct guesses.
Activity.SST: Eat 1 full-sized carrot, celery, bell pepper, or tomato
Activity.MSG: Perform a song. Full volume. Background music. You may read lyrics. The song must have lyrics.
Activity.JJP: Write thoughts and observations of the city. Write in complete sentences. Observations must be true and non-repetitive.
Activity.SNM: Hit a piece of pork with a brick, rock, or bottle. The pork may stay in its wrapper.
Activity.UIC:
Take a practice US citizenship test

https://www.uscis.gov/citizenship-resource-center/naturalization-test-and-study-resources/study-for-the-test/2008-civics-practice-test
Activity.BGP: Cast any liquid into a solid in a mold (Bogardus pinoeered cast iron architecture). This liquid does not need to be liquid when you acquire it. What constitutes a mold is interpreted loosely.
Activity.ACP: Sail a makeshift boat the full length of the fountain. If the fountain is empty, you may mark your score as 0.
Activity.CHT: Eat an entire order of jello or pudding with chopsticks. One partner must pass each piece the other partner. The jello or pudding must be at least the area of a credit card. If the jello or pudding is dropped, it must be picked back up by the first player. Jello and pudding are commonly available in dim sum restaurants.
Activity.DSQ: Do hopscotch blindfolded. Don't hit the lines. Repeat if you finish without hitting any lines.
Activity.BBR: All players on the team do a plank. Your score is the total time your team spent planking (nonconsecutive). For time to count, your entire team must be planking.
Activity.FHM: Give a >1 min speech petitioning the government for a redress of greviences while bearing your arms. Your score is the number of people peaceably assembled who acknowledge your speech.
Activity.MUP: Copy a 1'x1' section of the mural. Your partner must find it in one guess. Your score is the total time spent drawing and searching.
Activity.TPS: Build a bridge out of any material. Your score is the distance it spans.
Activity.BLW: Climb a fence or wall. A fence or wall is defined as any structure designed to impede a person's movement.
Activity.FMW: Take a rubbing using a pencil/pen/crayon. Your partner must find it. Your score is the total time spent creating and searching.
Activity.AHG:
Perform the first three stanzas of Hamilton:

How does a bastard, orphan, son of a whore and a Scotsman, dropped in the middle of a forgotten spot in the Caribbean by providence, impoverished, in squalor, grow up to be a hero and a scholar?
The ten-dollar founding father without a father got a lot farther by working a lot harder, by being a lot smarter, by being a self-starter, by fourteen, they placed him in charge of a trading charter. 
And every day while slaves were being slaughtered and carted away across the waves, he struggled and kept his guard up. Inside, he was longing for something to be a part of, the brother was ready to beg, steal, borrow or barter.
Activity.BTR: Guess the country of origin of tourists, one at a time. Ask them to confirm. If they are American, you must guess the state. New Yorkers are not worth any points.

Score.XIA: Total time drawing and finding (seconds, lowest)
Score.NSF: Sum of price per pound of correctly guessed fish (highest)
Score.NYM: Length of the tied food, before tying (cm, shortest)
